sentence: Looking at units outstanding versus one week prior within the universe of ETFs covered at ETF Channel, the biggest outflow was seen in the Consumer Staples Select Sector SPDR Fund ( XLP ), where 10,750,000 units were destroyed, or a 6.4% decrease week over week.
Among the largest underlying components of XLP, in morning trading today Procter & Gamble Company ( PG ) is up about 0.2%, and Coca-Cola Company ( KO ) is up by about 0.4%.

And on a percentage change basis, the ETF with the biggest outflow was the First Trust Multi Cap Growth AlphaDEX Fund ( FAD ), which lost 449,998 of its units, representing a 22.0% decline in outstanding units compared to the week prior.
Among the largest underlying components of FAD, in morning trading today Ulta Salon Cosmetics & Fragrance ( ULTA ) is up about 0.2%, and Lam Research Corporation (LRCX) is up by about 0.1%.
